---
Syntax: recite <scroll>
        recite <scroll> <target>

Reads aloud a magical scroll, releasing the spells inscribed upon it. Scrolls
hold up to three spell effects. All effects are released simultaneously and
the scroll is consumed in the process.

Without a target argument, spells are cast on yourself. With a target, the
scroll's effects are directed at the named character or object in the room.

Examples:
  recite identify     -- Recites a scroll of identify on yourself.
  recite curse goblin -- Recites a curse scroll targeting a goblin.

Restrictions:
  - The item must be in your inventory (carried, not worn).
  - The item must be of type SCROLL.
  - Target (if specified) must be in the same room.

See also: quaff brandish identify
